// AVL trees (BST Trees + rotate rules)
// A tree is unbalanced when: abs(height(left)-height(right)) > 1
// This can be repaired by a single rotation:
// 1. if left subtree too deep, rotate right
// 2. if right subtree too deep, rotate left
use 12 10 8 6 4 2 create AVL tree

12   -->     12     -->     10    -->     10    -->     10     -->     6
            /               /\            /\            /\            / \
           10              8  12         8  12         6  12         4   10
                                        /             / \           /    /\
                                       6             4   8         2    8  12